    <h1>SIN&#xAD;GA&#xAD;PORE&#x2019;S LIT&#xAD;TLE THAI&#xAD;LAND</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201222/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-22"><time>2020-12-22</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | TRAVEL</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Golden Mile Com­plex is known as Sin­ga­pore’s “Lit­tle Thai­land” for good rea­son.</p>
    <p>Its first storey smells of grilled pork, ow­ing to the mookata eater­ies that abound, and its third storey is lined with Thai mas­sage shops, well­ness spas and beauty sa­lons.</p>
    <p>Thai Su­per­mar­ket on the sec­ond storey of­fers a mind-bog­gling ar­ray of pastes from tamarind to vege­tar­ian Thai chilli. There is even an aisle largely ded­i­cated to fish sauce.</p>
    <p>I am con­stantly amazed at the va­ri­ety of snacks found here, from de­hy­drated lon­gans to crys­tallised ginger. Best of all, just like in Thai­land, the prices are rea­son­able.</p>

